logicz: The aim of this level is to collect as many diamonds as possible. %% Green diamondz are worth 1, blue diamondz 5 and purple 20 %% so be sure to find as many as possible!
Welcome to dizGruntled Alpha 2.0! Select a Grunt with the left %% mouse button and right click on a free tile to move it there. %% Use the arrow keys to scroll around the map.
Watch out for holez! Being made of clay, Gruntz aren't the %% brightest of the class and they'll walk right into them if you're %% not careful with your mouse...
Rolling balls will... well, splat Gruntz. Don't be dumb.

That green square there is a Switch. You know, the type that you %% stand on. This one will lower green pyramidz, but make sure %% Gruntz aren't standing on them when they raise because %% things could start looking nasty.
You've probably guessed from the icon on the silver switch %% *cough* what these pyramids do. Be quick!
Switches with the jump arrow only need to be pressed and they'll  %% stay toggled. Remember, different coloured switches have an %% effect on different coloured objects...
The symbols on the pressure plates tell you how many diamonds %% you must have in order to progress to the next section.
See that shiny bronze trophy over there? Well you could get %% your hands on another 2 of them following this path, though %% beware: don't use up your diamondz too early or you could %% get stuck!
Though you may loose control of Gruntz when they pass through %% fog, they'll walk straight through it if they can...
Look, some friends! %% Just a tip - you may wanna watch this switch.
I think some teamwork could come in useful here...
Notice how Gruntz always move diagonally when they can? %% Just a thought...
Time to harness the ancient power of Trial And Error.
LET THERE BE LIGHT! %% You really thought I could be bothered to fog the %% rest of the level? Wow...
Spiderz can only move on one axis, but will do so as soon %% as they see anything edible (they are usually disappointed).

Ah, the trusty hole can always be relied upon %% to stop those formidable enemies!
WELL THAT WAS CLEVER WASN'T IT, EH?
Ah, the hill, renowned for its view-obscuring capabilities...
Hmm, the Grunt by the trophies and his ability to save %% the game at arbitrary points in the level could %% really come in handy round about now...
Strange.. it seems the spiderz have a preference to %% move eastwards. If I believed in that kind of thing %% I'd say it was because they enjoy the morning sun.
I am quite speechless. Only 61 diamonds to go!
Finally, something that spiders can't navigate! %% You may want to be quick about this one...
